# Intelligence Architecture

Not yet implemented. Prototype was in src/ (now compact/src/).
Confidence varies by component.


## Field Model (the "weights")

3-tier structure replacing 140GB neural weights:

  Shell 1 density: 81 bins (3⁴), log-counts, L1-resident (~648 bytes)
  Shell 2 density: 625 bins (5⁴), log-counts, L3-resident (~5 KB)
  Reverse index: 625 bins × ~160 entries avg, coordinate-indexed

Total hot path: ~58 KB (fits L1/L2). One-pass construction, no training.
Log-counts normalize frequency (TF-IDF style): 5M vs 50 → ~10:1 ratio.


## RC Decay Attention

Replaces transformer 1/sqrt(d_k) constant scaling with per-token decay:

  relevance = exp(-t / (R × C))

  C = |μ| (substance weight) — nouns persist, articles decay fast
  R = base impedance + clause boundary penalty

4 dimensional heads (τ/χ/μ/φ), each attends ONLY along its dimension.
4D problem → four 1D problems. ~25% sparsity (75% near-zero).

Prediction: 4 dimensional heads outperform 4 arbitrary heads at equal
parameter count. RC-decay handles long documents better than fixed windows.


## Residual-Shift Generation

Walk = polynomial. Each word = monomial term. Generation:

  1. walk_sum = Σ all word coordinates so far
  2. centroid = walk_sum / walk_len
  3. prediction = attention context
  4. residual = prediction - centroid
  5. target = prediction + residual × 0.5 (shift away from center)
  6. Reverse lookup: find word nearest to target coordinate

Prevents repetition/collapse. The residual IS the next term in the
Taylor expansion — the walk extends the polynomial.


## Force Stabilization

When predicted coordinate has zero forces (origin), dispatch by previous:
  prev had π → expect ∮ (read → loop)
  prev had ∮ → expect π (loop → read)
  prev had ∘ → expect ∮ (call → loop)

Ensures walks never stall. Forces alternate naturally.


## Dark Energy in Generation

Empty/sparse field bins attract predictions. Score boost proportional
to 1/(1 + bin_count). Under-represented regions pull predictions toward
them. The vacuum is not inert — it creates pressure toward novelty.


